## 🛡️ General Cyber Safety Tips

- [ ] **1.** Never pay money to claim a prize, job offer, or reward — legitimate offers are always free
- [ ] **2.** Use strong passwords — minimum 8 characters with uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols
- [ ] **3.** Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) on every account — email, social media, and banking apps
- [ ] **4.** Do not click on unknown or suspicious links received via WhatsApp, SMS, or email
- [ ] **5.** Always verify the sender's identity before responding to any request for money or personal details
- [ ] **6.** Keep your social media accounts set to **Private** — review privacy settings regularly

---

## 💸 UPI & Financial Safety Tips *(Specific to Indian College Students)*

- [ ] **7.** Never share your UPI PIN, OTP, or bank password with anyone — not even bank employees
- [ ] **8.** Enable daily transaction limits and spending caps in your UPI / banking app
- [ ] **9.** Always double-check the recipient's UPI ID or phone number before sending money
- [ ] **10.** Be suspicious of "collect request" on UPI apps — you should never need to enter your PIN to *receive* money

---

## 📱 Social Media & Account Safety

- [ ] **11.** Use different passwords for different accounts — never reuse the same password
- [ ] **12.** Log out from shared or public devices after every session
- [ ] **13.** Do not share personal information like phone number, address, or Aadhaar details publicly
- [ ] **14.** Regularly review which apps have access to your Google / Facebook account and revoke unused ones

